{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Government to maintain VAT relief on repairs for historic churches",
        "additional_details": "The LPWGS, which has provided \u00a3300m+ since 2014 to cover VAT on repairs, ended on March 31, 2026 after its final \u00a323m was spent. A new \u00a392m fund over four years, limited to England and competitive, falls short of what is needed. We believe historic churches will as a result face financial strain, risking closures, neglect, and loss of heritage.",
        "background": "We urgently call on the Government to maintain the Listed Places of Worship Grant Scheme (LPWGS) and VAT relief on church repairs. Not doing so, we believe, adds a 20% tax burden on struggling congregations, threatening historic churches and signalling reduced support for Christian institutions.",
